identiality","Share information only with immediate family","Obtain parental permission first","Require partner consent for contraception","Document discussion with next of kin"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Erespect patient autonomy and maintain confidentiality\u003C/strong\u003E. Adult patients have the right to make autonomous decisions about their healthcare and to expect that their medical information will be kept confidential. This is a fundamental principle of medical ethics and is protected by law.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EShare information only with immediate family\u003C/strong\u003E would violate patient confidentiality and autonomy, even if limited to close relatives.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObtain parental permission first\u003C/strong\u003E is inappropriate as the patient is an adult and can make independent healthcare decisions.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequire partner consent for contraception\u003C/strong\u003E undermines patient autonomy as adult women have the right to make independent healthcare decisions.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument discussion with next of kin\u003C/strong\u003E violates both confidentiality and the patient\u0027s explicit request for privacy.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers have an ethical and legal obligation to maintain patient confidentiality and respect patient autonomy. This includes protecting private medical information and supporting patients in making informed decisions about their own healthcare.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The right to informed consent requires that patients receive adequate information about procedures, risks, benefits and alternatives before making healthcare decisions.","Women have the right to make autonomous decisions about their own healthcare, including refusing treatment.","Healthcare providers must respect patient confidentiality and privacy in accordance with legal and ethical obligations."],"references":["Mandal J, Ponnambath DK, Parija SC. Bioethics: A brief review. Trop Parasitol. 2017;7(1):5-7. doi:10.4103/tp.TP_4_17","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. doi:10.1159/000509119"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60866"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18072"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60866","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60866"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T16:39:15+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T16:50:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10786"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75358"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"gr